<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="2" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="1.[94,719,1114,1267]" lastBlockId="1.[794,1418,218,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1885" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1885" box="[260,569,1114,1139]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[260,397,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plectonotum</emphasis>
Gorham, 1885
</taxonomicName>
, was erected for 
<taxonomicName authority="Gorham, 1885" authorityName="Gorham" authorityYear="1885" box="[132,392,1146,1171]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labiale">
<emphasis box="[132,225,1146,1171]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. labiale</emphasis>
Gorham, 1885
</taxonomicName>
, based on the singular lateral bead of the pronotum. Among the Neotropical genera of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brancucci" authorityYear="1980" box="[127,342,1210,1235]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Dysmorphocerinae">Dysmorphocerinae</taxonomicName>
, this genus is also characterized by: small size, usually under 6.0 mm; elongate and fee- bly convex body shape; slender antennae without deformed antennomeres; elytra without foveate punctations aligned in striae; apical margin of pygidium with two conical lateral tubercles variably developed; peculiar morphology of the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[794,1418,218,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
The aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[1000,1150,378,403]" captionStart="Figures 116-118" captionStartId="19.[94,162,1469,1494]" captionTargetBox="[178,1336,804,1434]" captionTargetId="figure-285@19.[170,1342,803,1439]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="Figures 116-118.Plectonotumamazonas sp.nov.,aedeagus in dorsal,dorso-lateral and lateralview (transmittedlight).Abbreviations:ava = apico-ventral apoph-" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4637645" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4637645/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Figs. 116-118</figureCitation>
) displays the characters of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brancucci" authorityYear="1980" box="[881,1096,410,435]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Dysmorphocerinae">Dysmorphocerinae</taxonomicName>
, derived from the trilobed Elateroidea 
<typeStatus box="[933,986,442,467]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">type</typeStatus>
: tegmen with a distinct phallobase 
<emphasis box="[794,857,474,499]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">(phb),</emphasis>
and with the apical part projecting backwards in two lateral lobes or parameres 
<emphasis box="[1160,1207,506,531]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">(llb),</emphasis>
lateral lobes ventrally attached to a pair of joined apico-ventral apophysis 
<emphasis box="[845,906,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">(ava),</emphasis>
median lobe 
<emphasis box="[1076,1138,570,595]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">(mlb),</emphasis>
basally developed, and sheathed between two thin lateral sclerites 
<emphasis box="[1271,1320,602,627]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">(lsc),</emphasis>
lamellar, sagittal oriented,tapered,internal sac usually with a sclerotized apical part 
<emphasis box="[998,1056,666,691]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">(msi),</emphasis>
sheathed between the lamina of the two lateral sclerites.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[794,1418,218,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
The members of the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[1132,1269,730,755]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1132,1269,730,755]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plectonotum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are distribut- ed all over the Neotropical region between 
<collectingCountry box="[1279,1368,762,787]" name="Panama" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Panama</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[794,850,794,819]" name="Chile" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Chile</collectingCountry>
with nearly fifty valid species. The first identification key for species was written by 
<bibRefCitation author="Pic, M." box="[1187,1298,826,851]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="174 - 175" refId="ref19478" refString="Pic, M. 1911. Contribution a l'etude du genre &quot; Plectonotum &quot; Gorham. L'Echange, 27: 174 - 175; 178 - 180." type="journal article" year="1911">Pic (1911)</bibRefCitation>
. Later, one additional 
<taxonomicName box="[911,1048,858,883]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[911,1048,858,883]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plectonotum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species was described from 
<collectingCountry box="[1357,1417,858,883]" name="Brazil" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[800,963,890,915]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="419 - 432" refId="ref19755" refString="Wittmer, W. 1967. 28. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der neotropischen Malacodermata (Coleoptera). Studia Entomologica (Petropolis), 10 (1 - 4): 419 - 432." type="journal article" year="1967">Wittmer, 1967</bibRefCitation>
). Further, a key was given for the species occurring in 
<collectingCountry box="[935,1009,922,947]" name="Bolivia" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
and south 
<collectingCountry box="[1135,1185,922,947]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Peru</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[1198,1362,922,947]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="325 - 341" refId="ref19826" refString="Wittmer, W. 1988. 40. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der neotropischen Fauna (Coleoptera, Cantharidae und Malachiidae). Entomologica Basiliensia, 12: 325 - 341." type="journal article" year="1988">Wittmer, 1988</bibRefCitation>
). The species of 
<collectingCountry box="[917,1008,954,979]" name="Ecuador" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
were keyed in contributions to the 
<taxonomicName box="[794,931,986,1011]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[794,931,986,1011]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plectonotum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
of 
<collectingCountry box="[971,1062,986,1011]" name="Ecuador" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Ecuador</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Constantin, R." box="[1077,1271,986,1011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="49 - 74" refId="ref19085" refString="Constantin, R. 2008. A contribution to the genus Plectonotum Gorham, 1891, in Ecuador (Coleoptera, Cantharidae). Entomologica Basiliensia et Collectionis Frey, 30: 49 - 74." type="journal article" year="2008">Constantin, 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Constantin, R." box="[1283,1342,986,1011]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="7 - 29" refId="ref19121" refString="Constantin, R. 2010. A contribution to knowledge of the Cantharidae (Coleoptera, Elateroidea) in Ecuador and French Guiana. Entomologica Basiliensia et Collectionis Frey, 32: 7 - 29." type="journal article" year="2010">2010</bibRefCitation>
). From 
<collectingCountry box="[794,847,1018,1043]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Peru</collectingCountry>
, only six species were previously known (
<bibRefCitation author="Constantin, R. &amp; Chaboo, C. S." pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="2" refId="ref19157" refString="Constantin, R. &amp; Chaboo, C. S. 2016. Beetles (Coleoptera) of Peru: A Survey of the Families. Cantharidae Imhoff, 1856. Journal of the Kansas Entomological Society, 89 (2): 195 - 20." type="journal article" year="2016">Constantin &amp; Chaboo, 2016</bibRefCitation>
): 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1988" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1988" box="[1002,1414,1050,1075]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="howdeni">
<emphasis box="[1002,1242,1050,1075]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Plectonotum howdeni</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[1252,1414,1050,1075]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="325 - 341" refId="ref19826" refString="Wittmer, W. 1988. 40. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der neotropischen Fauna (Coleoptera, Cantharidae und Malachiidae). Entomologica Basiliensia, 12: 325 - 341." type="journal article" year="1988">Wittmer, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1988" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1988" box="[794,1025,1082,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inca">
<emphasis box="[794,861,1082,1107]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. inca</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[867,1025,1082,1107]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="325 - 341" refId="ref19826" refString="Wittmer, W. 1988. 40. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der neotropischen Fauna (Coleoptera, Cantharidae und Malachiidae). Entomologica Basiliensia, 12: 325 - 341." type="journal article" year="1988">Wittmer, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Pic, 1927)" baseAuthorityName="Pic" baseAuthorityYear="1927" box="[1035,1318,1082,1107]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longissimum">
<emphasis box="[1035,1194,1082,1107]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. longissimum</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Pic, M." box="[1208,1312,1082,1107]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="139 - 140" refId="ref19528" refString="Pic, M. 1927. Nouveaux Coleopteres exotiques. Bulletin de la Societe entomologique de France, 139 - 140." type="book chapter" year="1927">Pic, 1927</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1988" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="martinezi">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. martinezi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[843,1000,1114,1139]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="325 - 341" refId="ref19826" refString="Wittmer, W. 1988. 40. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der neotropischen Fauna (Coleoptera, Cantharidae und Malachiidae). Entomologica Basiliensia, 12: 325 - 341." type="journal article" year="1988">Wittmer, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1967" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1967" box="[1010,1307,1114,1139]" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruanum">
<emphasis box="[1010,1143,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. peruanum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[1149,1307,1114,1139]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="419 - 432" refId="ref19755" refString="Wittmer, W. 1967. 28. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der neotropischen Malacodermata (Coleoptera). Studia Entomologica (Petropolis), 10 (1 - 4): 419 - 432." type="journal article" year="1967">Wittmer, 1967</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer, 1988" authorityName="Wittmer" authorityYear="1988" class="Insecta" family="Cantharidae" genus="Plectonotum" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ruficolle">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">P. ruficolle</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wittmer, W." box="[861,1018,1146,1171]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2" pagination="325 - 341" refId="ref19826" refString="Wittmer, W. 1988. 40. Beitrag zur Kenntnis der neotropischen Fauna (Coleoptera, Cantharidae und Malachiidae). Entomologica Basiliensia, 12: 325 - 341." type="journal article" year="1988">Wittmer, 1988</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="1.[794,1418,218,1267]" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">
Fourteen new species are described below and a new key is proposed here for separating the twenty species currently known from 
<collectingCountry box="[1040,1093,1242,1267]" name="Peru" pageId="1" pageNumber="2">Peru</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
